ADD A REPLICATED DATABASE

This form is used to define a database that will become part of your
replication scheme.

To complete this screen, enter the appropriate values for the desired
database.  Use the Tab key to move from one field to the next. If you
make an error, you can use the Clear operation to reset the entire form.
To save the definition, select the Save operation.

The fields on the form are:

        FIELD NAME              DESCRIPTION
        ----------              -----------
        Database Number         A mandatory field to specify a unique
                                number within the whole replication
                                system.  The number assigned is used as
                                part of the replicated transaction key
                                for transactions originated from this
                                database.  Valid range from 1 to 32,767.

        Virtual Node Name       A mandatory field to specify the virtual
                                node (vnode) name, as defined in the
                                Ingres/Net netutil utility, used
                                to connect to the database.

        Database Name           The name of the database.

        Database Owner          The owner (DBA) of the database.

        DBMS Type               The type of DBMS, for example,
                                Ingres or CA-Datacom.  Use
                                ListChoices to view acceptable values.

        Remarks                 A short comment.


The menu commands are as follows:

        MENU COMMAND    SYNOPSIS
        ------------    --------
        Save            Save the definition and return to the Database
                        Summary screen.

        Clear           Reset the values entered.  You will be asked to
                        confirm before the form is cleared.

        ListChoices     Display a list of acceptable values for the
                        current field.

        Help            Access the Help facility.

        End             Return to the Database Summary screen.
